    "stem": "\\(x\\) and \\(y\\) are positive numbers. \\(x\\) is increased by \\(y\\%\\), and separately \\(y\\) is increased by \\(x\\%\\).",
    "quantityA": "The result of increasing \\(x\\) by \\(y\\%\\)",
    "quantityB": "The result of increasing \\(y\\) by \\(x\\%\\)",
    "answer": "C",
    "solutionStandard": "Increasing \\(x\\) by \\(y\\%\\) gives \\(x + \\frac{xy}{100} = x\\left(1+\\frac{y}{100}\\right)\\). Increasing \\(y\\) by \\(x\\%\\) gives \\(y\\left(1+\\frac{x}{100}\\right) = y + \\frac{xy}{100}\\). Both expressions equal \\(x + y + \\frac{xy}{100}\\), so they are always equal.",
